# safeguard-panic — start here

**Before editing this project, read `CAPSULES.md` at the repository root first.** It has the five capsules (overview, implementation, reliability, Git/GitHub, next steps).

**One-line summary:** Vite + React (`apps/client`) — panic flow + Iceman map (`MapView`, nearby-signals sheet, pin hover popups); adapters in **`apps/client/src/panic/panicServices.ts`**; panic UI in **`PanicFlow.tsx`** + **`PanicFlow.css`**. Repo also includes merged **`backend/`** for server-side work.

**Do not casually remove** panic reliability patterns: pointer capture, inflight/finish/confirm-send mutexes, stop-before-start, window pointer fallback, reduced-motion and touch CSS — details in `CAPSULES.md` section 3.

**Git:** `origin` is `https://github.com/bnha4212/Hack-Davis-Ice-Man.git`; work on **`main`**; avoid **force push** unless the team explicitly agrees.
